=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from 4-bromo-2-aminophenol (Nc1cc(Br)ccc1O) and protect the aniline as the trifluoroacetamide with (CF3CO)2O or CF3COCl/pyridine to give O=C(Nc1cc(Br)ccc1O)C(F)(F)F | Step 2: O-alkylate this phenol with tert-butyl bromoacetate (BrCH2CO2tBu) using K2CO3 or Cs2CO3 in DMF/acetone to form tert-butyl 2-(4-bromo-2-trifluoroacetamidophenoxy)acetate, CC(C)(C)OC(=O)COc1cc(Br)ccc1NC(=O)C(F)(F)F | Step 3: Nitrate the protected aryl ether under controlled conditions (e.g. HNO3/Ac2O or cold HNO3/H2SO4) to install NO2 at the 5-position, giving CC(C)(C)OC(=O)COc1cc(Br)cc([N+](=O)[O-])c1NC(=O)C(F)(F)F | Step 4: Remove the trifluoroacetyl group by mild basic hydrolysis (K2CO3 in MeOH/H2O or NH3/MeOH) to reveal the free aniline while retaining the tert-butyl ester, affording the target CC(C)(C)OC(=O)COc1cc(Br)cc([N+](=O)[O-])c1N.

